{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62818838-de6b-4038-acb5-7c29cc211206","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2. Here's the recommended modern pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest 3.x+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization — runs after constructor, before each test\n    public Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup work here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup — runs after each test\n    public Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async teardown here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` is supported in MSTest 3.x+ (no need for the property setter pattern).\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement for async per-test setup (replaces `[TestInitialize]` for async scenarios).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — implement for async per-test teardown.\n- You can still use `[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]` for one-time static setup if needed.\n\nThis avoids the older `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern and the `[TestInitialize] async Task` workaround.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0e1ac243-364b-43f5-86f0-f91b504a166f","outputTokens":405,"requestId":"E3C1:182BD0:181D125:1AFE946:6A05284B"},"id":"cd3010a8-019f-4485-bc88-bebb480ceb0b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:41:40.802Z","parentId":"1b22224b-ccda-406e-9a9a-8f93c3c69ae9"}
